title: Top Performer in Control of Corruption
description: In 2023, Finland achieved a perfect score of 100 in the Control of Corruption percentile rank, indicating the highest level of integrity and transparency in governance worldwide.

title: Exceptional Air Quality
description: With a mean annual PM2.5 exposure of 4.9 micrograms per cubic meter in 2020, Finland ranks among the countries with the cleanest air globally.

title: Universal Financial Inclusion for Older Adults
description: As of 2021, 100% of Finland's population aged 25 and older have access to financial institutions or mobile money services, showcasing complete financial inclusion.

title: Universal Financial Inclusion for Educated Population
description: In 2021, Finland achieved a 100% account ownership rate among individuals with secondary education or higher, reflecting widespread financial access.

title: High Investment in Research and Development
description: In 2020, 71% of Finnish firms invested in R&D, highlighting a strong commitment to innovation and technological advancement.

title: Efficient Logistics Performance
description: Finland scored 4.1 in the ease of arranging competitively priced shipments in 2022, indicating a robust logistics infrastructure.

title: Reliable Shipment Delivery
description: In 2022, Finland achieved a score of 4.3 for the frequency of shipments reaching consignees on time, reflecting high reliability in logistics.

title: Strong Rule of Law
description: Finland's rule of law estimate reached 1.97 in 2023, placing it among the top countries for legal integrity and justice.

title: High Female School Enrollment
description: In 2022, Finland's female secondary school enrollment rate was 153.24%, indicating a highly inclusive educational system.

title: Low Mortality from Air Pollution
description: In 2019, Finland reported a mortality rate of 7.4 per 100,000 due to air pollution, one of the lowest globally.

title: High Contraceptive Prevalence
description: In 2015, 85.47% of married women in Finland used some form of contraception, reflecting effective family planning services.

title: Minimal Child Marriage
description: As of 2017, only 0.1% of Finnish women aged 20-24 were married by age 18, indicating strong protection of children's rights.
